            <h2><a href="/news-events/articles/2024/05-may/2024-rsc-elections-voting-open/">Voting open in RSC elections as members get chance to select new President</a></h2>
<p><em>29 April 2024</em> Members have until 23 May to submit their ballots and decide who will fill 11 posts across the RSC.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="text-image-block__img">
            
        <noscript data-slimmage="true" data-img-class="slimmage hashtaglink" data-img-src="https://epi-rsc.rsc-cdn.org/globalassets/07-news-events/rsc-news/news-articles/2024/05-may/rsc-elections-2024/c_ad-hoc_2024_rsc-elections-assets_4_1600x1200px.jpg?version=c6b6c45b&amp;width=800&amp;format=jpg&amp;quality=80" data-img-alt="image block"><img class="slimmage hashtaglink" src="https://epi-rsc.rsc-cdn.org/globalassets/07-news-events/rsc-news/news-articles/2024/05-may/rsc-elections-2024/c_ad-hoc_2024_rsc-elections-assets_4_1600x1200px.jpg?version=c6b6c45b&amp;width=800&amp;format=jpg&amp;quality=80" alt="RSC chief executive Dr Helen Pain, Scottish Minister for Higher and Further Education Graeme Dey MSP, and RSC president Professor Gill Reid stand in front of an RSC banner that says &#39;Science and the Parliament&#39; inside Our Dynamic Earth in Edinburgh, Scotland" alt="image block"></noscript>


